            "id": "a243a540ac8d4e83bff5c",
            "questionText": "A spoonful of sugar with a mass of $!$m_s$!$ grams is added to a cup of hot tea with a volume of $!$V_t$!$ mL at a temperature of $!$T_t$!$ \\( ^\\circ \\text{C} \\) (above which the sugar dissolves rapidly). Experimental data indicate that the sugar dissolves completely in the tea in $!$t$!$ seconds when $!$m_s$!$, $!$V_t$!$, and $!$T_t$!$ have the given values. Assuming that the time required for the sugar to dissolve, $!$t$!$, is directly proportional to the mass of the sugar and inversely proportional to both the volume and the temperature of the tea, determine the value of $!$t$!$ (in seconds) required for complete dissolution when the proportionality constant is $!$k$!$. Please provide the numerical values for $!$m_s$!$, $!$V_t$!$, $!$T_t$!$, and $!$k$!$ so that a single numerical answer for $!$t$!$ can be calculated.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "5ffef3834b554f6b9e62f",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by recalling the relationship between the dissolution time $!$t$!$, the sugar mass $!$m_s$!$, the tea volume $!$V_t$!$, the tea temperature $!$T_t$!$, and the proportionality constant $!$k$!$. Choose the option that correctly represents the proportionality given in the problem.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "6d8df52d-412e-48a3-933f-d18a961c927e"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$t = k \\cdot \\frac{m_s}{V_t \\cdot T_t}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$t = k \\cdot \\frac{V_t \\cdot T_t}{m_s}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$t = k \\cdot \\frac{m_s \\cdot V_t}{T_t}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
